request.description:
Query all 3 key checkout-api metrics in a single PromQL query (or-chained).

Note: Set {{start_ts}} and {{end_ts}} collection variables to Unix epoch timestamps.
Add a Pre-request Script to auto-set them:
  pm.collectionVariables.set('start_ts', Math.floor(Date.now()/1000) - 900);
  pm.collectionVariables.set('end_ts', Math.floor(Date.now()/1000));

Returns JSON with all metric time-series data.

query.description:
Start timestamp in NANOSECONDS (Loki requires nanoseconds, not seconds).

Add Pre-request Script:
  const nowNs = Date.now() * 1_000_000;
  pm.collectionVariables.set('end_ts_ns', nowNs.toString());
  pm.collectionVariables.set('start_ts_ns', (nowNs - BigInt(900_000_000_000)).toString());

request.description:
Fetch log lines from Lok for the checkout-api service.

Returns JSON with log entries grouped by stream (label set).

Loki uses NANOSECOND timestamps (Unix epoch × 1,000,000,000).
Example: 1700000000 seconds → 1700000000000000000 nanoseconds.

Add a Pre-request Script to auto-set timestamps:
  const now = Date.now();
  const nowNs = now * 1_000_000;                 // milliseconds → nanoseconds
  const startNs = nowNs - 15 * 60 * 1_000_000_000; // 15 minutes ago
  pm.collectionVariables.set('start_ts_ns', startNs.toString());
  pm.collectionVariables.set('end_ts_ns', nowNs.toString());

